# .vercelignore (D-02 — LAUNCH-01 / LAUNCH-10)
#
# The Vercel CLI uploads the working tree (NOT git history) on `vercel --prod`, filtered by
# THIS file. PRECEDENCE: when a .vercelignore exists the CLI uses it INSTEAD of .gitignore —
# they are NOT merged. So this list is self-sufficient: it cannot assume any .gitignore pattern
# still applies, which is why the local env files + caches below are explicitly re-covered.
# Vercel still applies its own built-in defaults (node_modules, .next, .git), but .env.local is
# re-listed here as a belt-and-suspenders secret-leak guard (T-23-04).
#
# DO NOT add `scripts/`, `src/`, `public/`, `next.config.ts`, `package.json`, or `.env.example`
# here — the build/`prebuild` runs `scripts/check-env.mjs`, and `public/` serves og-default.png,
# the Inter .ttf fonts, and the landing showcase webp (src/components/landing/proof.tsx). D-03:
# NO vercel.json — CSP/HSTS headers ship in next.config.ts headers() from Phase 16.

# Planning corpus + docs + DB migrations + test suites never ship to the runtime bundle.
# (supabase/ is safe to exclude: prod DB is provisioned out-of-band via `db push` from the
# dev machine — see docs/runbooks/launch.md — never from the Vercel build.)
#
# LEADING SLASH IS LOAD-BEARING: an unanchored `supabase/` matches a `supabase` dir at ANY
# depth — which silently excludes `src/lib/supabase/` (client/server/middleware/service-role)
# and breaks the Vercel build with 58 "Can't resolve '@/lib/supabase/*'" errors. The local
# build never catches it (nothing is excluded locally). Anchor every top-level dir to root.
/.planning/
/docs/
/supabase/
/tests/
/e2e/

# Local env + caches — re-covered here because .vercelignore replaces .gitignore (precedence).
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.log
.lighthouseci/
